<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="898" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d898">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00 Bandit Activities, 1931/207</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-20">July 20, 1931</date>.<lb/>[Received July
                                30.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 431</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that the
                            Brigade Commander has informed me of an engagement on July 9, 1931,
                            between a Guardia patrol under Lieutenant Clark, Guardia Nacional
                            (Corporal, U. S. Marine Corps), and Lieutenant Martinez, Guardia
                            Nacional, and a small group of bandits near Telpaneca in the Department
                            of Nueva Segovia. One bandit was killed and three were wounded. There
                            were no Guardia casualties. The Guardia captured one pistol and
                            miscellaneous articles from the bandits.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Matthew E. Hanna</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
